   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER THREE AN EXTRACT</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>OF THE BASIC DIVINE REVELATION</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>IN THE HOLY SCRIPTURES OUTLINE To know the processed and consummated Triune God Matt 28:19: Incarnated to be the flesh the first God-man to express God in humanity John 1:14.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Anointed to be the Christ, the anointed One of God, to accomplish God's plan in His eternal economy Luke 4:18.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Consummated to be the life-giving Spirit to apply what Christ has accomplished 1 Cor 15:45b.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>To know the all-inclusive Christ: As the mystery of God to be the reality of the Triune God Col 2:2.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>As the Word of God to define God John 1:1.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>As the embodiment of God to express God Col 2:9.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>As the centrality and universality of God's eternal economy Col 1:13-19.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>As the God-allotted portion to be the enjoyment of His believers Col 1:12.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>As the life to His believers for them to live Him Col 3:4.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>As the Head of His Body for His expression Col 1:18.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>To know the consummated Spirit: As the transfiguration of Christ in resurrection 1 Cor 15:45b.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>As the compound Spirit, compounded with Christ's divinity, humanity, death with its effectiveness, and resurrection with its power as the elements to be the holy anointing ointment Exo 30:23-25.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>As the Spirit of life Rom 8:2.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>As the Spirit of God Rom 8:9.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>As the Spirit of Jesus Acts 16:7.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>As the Spirit of Christ Rom 8:9.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>As the Spirit of Jesus Christ Phil 1:19.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>As the indwelling Spirit Rom 8:11.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>As the pneumatic Christ Rom 8:10.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>To know the church: As the universal house of God to be God's manifestation in humanity 1 Tim 3:15-16.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>As the local churches to be the expression of the one church of God Rev 1:11; 1 Cor 10:32.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>As the universal Body of Christ to be His fullness Eph 1:22-23.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>To know the Body of Christ: The mystery of Christ Eph 3:4.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>The fullness of Him who fills all in all Eph 1:23.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>The organism of the Triune God, constituted with the Triune God and the believers Eph 4:4-6.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>The contents of the new man Col 3:10-11.</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>To be built up by the perfected saints in all the local churches Eph 4:11-12.</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>Not divided and not divisible 1 Cor 1:10-13.</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>To consummate the New Jerusalem.</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>To know the ultimate consummation the New Jerusalem Rev 21: A mystical constitution constituted with the processed and consummated Triune God with His chosen, redeemed, regenerated, transformed, and glorified people.</S>
   <S PAR='33' RSNT='1' SNO='33'>As the bride the wife of the Lamb vv.</S>
   <S PAR='34' RSNT='1' SNO='34'>2, 9.</S>
   <S PAR='35' RSNT='1' SNO='35'>As the tabernacle to be the eternal dwelling place of God v. 3.</S>
   <S PAR='36' RSNT='1' SNO='36'>As the temple to be the eternal dwelling place of the glorified saints v. 22.</S>
   <S PAR='37' RSNT='1' SNO='37'>As the eternal expansion and expression of the processed and consummated Triune God in the regenerated, transformed, and glorified humanity.</S>
   <S PAR='38' RSNT='1' SNO='38'>To know the self: As the old man, the natural man: Crucified with Christ on the cross Gal 2:20.</S>
   <S PAR='39' RSNT='1' SNO='39'>Buried with Christ in baptism Rom 6:4.</S>
   <S PAR='40' RSNT='1' SNO='40'>To be denied, condemned, and rejected all the time Matt 16:24.</S>
   </TEXT>
